It makes my day me wonder when I clean these cars how people can live like this and handle sitting in these cars every day.
 
Does the smell get to them?
 
Sticky cloth seats to your clothing cause concern?
 
Or just the amount of trash kicked out of the way everytime they climb in?
 
Truth is... I never will. For some its laziness to not care for the vehicle. Others it could be a mental illness issue and for them my heart goes out for them to seek help and just take care of themselves.
 
I will admit to having lazy tendencees time to time. We all get busy with life, kids, work and a slow progression of dirt can just happen before you know it.
 
As an old fart who is owned and driven a car for over 20+ years... here are some tips that help.
 
1. Getting gas? Throw away trash!
 
2. If you HAVE to eat in your car, chose easy/crumb free options.
 
3. Keep a microfiber towel in your car to even wipe off dust and dirt dry. That along makes a big difference.
 
4. Vacuum weekly (even if its 5 min). Good news here is all driveway big chain car washes offer free vacuums. USE THEM!
 
5. Invest small time to time to get all the essentials you need to keep your car clean. APC, Window cleaner, etc etc.
 
Below is an example of the recent detail I did that sparked this post. If these tips were helpful, go give it a watch or share these tips on your socials.
